  <brief_title>Sitosterolemia Extension Study (0653-004)(COMPLETED)</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Multicenter, Randomized, Double-Blind, Placebo-Controlled Study to Evaluate the Safety and Efficacy of MK0653 When Added to Current Regimen in Patients With Homozygous Sitosterolemia</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Merck Sharp &amp; Dohme Corp.</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Merck Sharp &amp; Dohme Corp.</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is an extension study for patients having unusually high absorption of non-cholesterol
      sterols, resulting in heart-related diseases. This study will evaluate the long term safety
      and the ability to lower cholesterol levels with an investigational drug.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The duration of treatment is 52 weeks.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
